The distal portion of the cones is composed of triactines and is commonly ornamented with tufts of diactines and trichoxeas (
Figures 6C, D
). In the tubar skeleton, there are triactines with the unpaired actine towards the distal region (
Figure 6E
). These spicules form an articulated skeleton, although rare scattered spicules are observed. The subatrial region is formed by few triactines with the unpaired actine choanosome-oriented. The atrial skeleton is formed mainly by triactines and few tetractines, so its surface is slightly hispid (
Figure 6F
).

